						               													<description>Step into the shoes of Doctor Watson&amp;#10;&amp;#10;A quiz game where players take turns attempting to answer puzzling questions in order to earn points.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;On their turn, a player chooses a card from one of four piles each representing a different difficulty level. The player then turns a sand timer and if they can correctly answer the question in time they score points. Either way, play then passes to the next player.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;More difficult questions are worth more points and each player has a single Moriarty card and a Sherlock card which can each be used once per game to score in additional ways. A Moriarty card is used at the start of another players turn as a bet that they will not answer the question correctly (or in time). If the bet is correct, the Moriarty player earns the points for the question. A Sherlock card can be used on your own turn to make the question worth double the points. However, it must be played before reading the question!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
